RT @Leadmill: We are so happy that the people of Sheffield & beyond want to make their voices heard!

Here's a few more of your reasons why‚Ä¶

@kiddyguest Many bands pose as indie while they are backed by majors. Once a band like this arrived in Worcester with a drum kit alone worth good 10k. It broke hearts of the local bands that played that night. We all knew they had major backing. I left before that band was on. Always will.

Now off to make a pepperoni and mushroom pizza. WH Murdocks and mine favourite food. 

You can go back to hyping bands all you want. Im done. xxx

As an A&R my loyalty is to those who have no money no connections  nobody to give them their first review. Thats what Vanadian was always about since I was a 16 year pld kid putting gig posters at my school walls. And thats how it will remain.

We are supposed to be champions not gate keepers, legend tellers. I dont agree and will not participate in hyping another label made act at the expense of kids that are life and blood of the circuit. 

There will never be consent from me on that. Call me a pariah I dont care.

Inclusivity, equal chances and opportunities are important to keep our industry healthy competent and real. We cannot kill peoples hopes ans dreams and tell them lies when the truth is its money and connections that get you ahead in music. Not your talent.

There more we feed them legends about hard work and talent while hyping bands with connections the more of them kids will jump. Whoever worked with young bands will tell you how desperate and depressed ppl are not reaching audiences. They see what we do. Action - reaction

Look you may think Im a hater or biased. But its unethical in my eyes to hype one band ad nauseum and tell people they did it all thanks to their own talent and hard work. Its lies.

There are kids out there who think they are worthless and tell me they want to jump under a train

And if calling it out makes me a Fox Mulder (or Courtney Love) of indie circuit then be it. Tho Id prefer to be HM Murdock of the indie circuit. BUT we need to he honest why some bands are everywhere while others never make it and its only connections and money.

Some bands do their utmost and are ignored, they all fight for scraps while well connected pop starlets go to stratosphere. It doesnt mean the rest of the circuit is bad and talentless. It just means they dont have connections ans MONEY to be noticed.

also lets start being honest on the circuit. If a band has BIG connections, BIG managers and BIG money to be promoted they are no indie. Lets not give kids in music colleges a warped understanding of what it means to have a break through. Connections make it easier to be noticed

Im no truther. I just dont wanna participate in hyping an industry plant that is also a weak band. Throw enough funds at any band in a pub and you can make them just as big. I dont buy funny, youth and inclusivity from starved blondes made 'popular' by gammons at a major.

@alanneilson Theres always a choice and ways to balance life, day job and music. It takes planning and arrangement but its possible. I dont think giving up your passion because your gf told you so and then putting the ambition on kids is healhy. Neither is regarding one self as retired at 30

@alanneilson The band I had in mind was told by their respective girlfriends that the party was over and real life bagan: ie marriage, kids and 'proper' jobs, they sold their equipment and now post on insta that their 2 yo kids are going to be rock stars instead. Heartbreaking.
